Date: February 9, 2026 (Updated)

**Prepared For:** C3scan.io Product Team (Attn: Ava)

**Scope:** Admin Tool & Customer Tool

Companion to: C3scan Web Apps Build Spec v0.2.3 (Admin \+ Customer)

## 0\. Document Control & How to Use

This UI/UX spec defines the visual system, components, and interaction patterns for C3scan Web Apps. Functional behavior (routes, permissions, API, enums, acceptance tests) lives in the Build Spec. When a screen is implemented, both documents must agree: Build Spec defines what; UI/UX Spec defines how it looks and feels.

### 0.1 Source of truth

• Build Spec v0.2.3: data model, status enums, permissions, endpoint contracts, acceptance tests.  
• UI/UX Spec v1.1 (this doc): tokens, components, layouts, responsive rules, and interaction standards.  
If there is a conflict, resolve by updating both docs in the same PR and bumping versions.

### 0.3 Nomenclature (Build Spec v0.2.3 aligned)

These terms show up across both apps, copy, and UI labels. This UI/UX spec uses them consistently:

- **Operator:** A coworking company that operates one or many Locations (example: Thinkspace).
- **Member:** Any person tied to a mailbox for operational or compliance reasons (may not have portal access).
- **Mailbox Manager:** The portal user who can act in the Customer Tool for a mailbox. A Mailbox Manager is always a Member.
- **Authorized Member:** A Member included in the USPS compliance roster for a company, even if they are not a portal user. Legal full name is stored in `company_alias.alias_name` where `alias_type = "authorized_member"`.

UI convention: prefer **Member** in headings and labels (not “Renter”). Use **Mailbox Manager** only when you are explicitly referring to portal permissions/actions.

### **1.1 The "Productivity" Aesthetic**

We are moving away from the "utility" feel of PilotoMail toward a modern, high-density enterprise aesthetic. We prioritize **clarity, whitespace, and hierarchy**.

* **Visual References:** Stripe Dashboard, Linear, Shopify Admin.  
* **Backgrounds:** Off-white/Gray surfaces (\#F7F9FC) to separate content from the browser chrome.  
* **Cards:** Pure white (\#FFFFFF) with subtle, soft shadows to float content.  
* **Branding (Electric Yellow):** Primary Brand Color \#FFCC00 (derived from logo). Used for **High-Impact Statuses**, **Focus States** (rings around active inputs), and **Brand Accents**.  
* **Typography:** Inter (Open Source) or SF Pro (Apple System) for high legibility.

### **1.2 Navigation: The "Command Center" Model**

Instead of the static sidebar shown in legacy screenshots, we use a minimal rail and a powerful **Command Palette**.

* **Global Hotkey:** CMD+K (Mac) or CTRL+K (Windows).  
* **Behavior:** Opens a centered modal to **Navigate** (e.g., "Go to Mailboxes"), **Search** (e.g., "Find PMB 1201"), or **Action** (e.g., "Upload Mail").  
* **Persistent Nav:** Minimal Left Rail (Icons only) to maximize screen real estate for the "Deep Work" areas.

### **1.3 Mobile Strategy: "Triage & Track"**

The Admin Tool is primarily for desktop workstations. The mobile view focuses strictly on floor tasks:

1. **Barcode/QR Scanner First:** Instant access to scan a package label.  
2. **Read-Only/Status Updates:** Quickly mark items as "Picked Up" or "Located."  
3. **No Configuration:** Complex settings and compliance reviews are hidden on mobile to reduce clutter.

### **2.2 Status Pills**

Status indicators use a **subtle background \+ strong text** style for readability.

| Status Group | Color | Mapped Statuses |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **New / Active** | Blue | uploaded, received |
| **Processing** | **Yellow** | open\_scan\_requested, forward\_requested, pickup\_requested |
| **Action Required** | **Red** | action\_required, non\_compliant |
| **Completed** | Green | open\_scan\_completed, forward\_shipped, picked\_up |
| **Disposed** | Gray | shred\_requested, disposed |
| Compliance | Purple | compliance\_pending, compliance\_submitted |
| Compliance | Red | non\_compliant, missing\_documents |
| Mailbox | Gray | cancelled, inactive |
| Request | Yellow | open\_scan\_requested, forward\_requested |
| Request | Blue | forward\_label\_created, open\_scan\_in\_progress |
| Request | Green | open\_scan\_completed, forward\_shipped |

## **3\. Admin Tool Specification**

*Target Audience: Location Staff, Admin Owners*

### **3.1 Dashboard ("The Cockpit")**

* **Goal:** Instant situational awareness.  
* **Layout:** 3-Column Grid.  
  1. **The Pulse (Top Row):** Simple metric cards (Pending Requests, Unprocessed Mail).  
  2. **Task Queue (Main Column):** Unified list of "Things to do right now" (e.g., "Open & Scan Request \- PMB 101").  
  3. **Recent Activity (Right Column):** Feed of system events.

### **3.2 Mail Item Detail ("Deep Work")**

* **Route:** /admin/mail/:mail\_item\_id  
* **Architecture:** Asymmetric Two-Column Split (Replaces the "drawer" pattern).  
* **Left Panel (Workspace):**  
  * Dark background (\#F0F2F5) to reduce glare.  
  * High-res viewer (Zoom/Rotate/Crop) for the envelope or content.  
  * **"Scan Mode" Drop Zone:** Appears dynamically when fulfilling an open\_scan request.  
* **Right Panel (Control Center):**  
  * White background.  
  * **Status Card:** High visibility (Yellow for Pending).  
  * **Action Deck:** Large buttons (Primary: "Complete Request", Secondary: "Reject").  
  * **Timeline:** Vertical history of the item (Uploaded \-\> Requested \-\> Completed).

### 3.3 Request Detail Views (Forward Mail & Open & Scan)

Route: /admin/requests/:request\_id  
Purpose: Single source of truth for fulfilling customer requests. Must show: request metadata, related mail item(s), customer-provided details (forward address), fulfillment artifacts (labels, scans), notes, and immutable activity trail.

### Required sections (matches reference UI)

• Header: status pill \+ primary action button (e.g., “Forward Mail” / “Mark as Completed”) and navigation controls.  
• Request meta: request type, Request ID, Mailbox, Mail ID.  
• Mail image preview: secure viewer.  
• Fulfillment panel (varies by type):  
   \- Forward Mail: recipient name \+ destination address \+ carrier selection \+ label/tracking.  
   \- Open & Scan: upload scanned files (PDF/JPG) \+ optional page count.  
• Upload Files: drag/drop zone that creates request attachments.  
• Notes: staff notes with timestamps.  
• Activity Trail: append-only event log (requested, updated, uploaded, completed).

## **4\. Customer Tool Specification**

*Target Audience: Mailbox Managers*

### **4.1 Compliance Wizard ("Focus Mode")**

* **Route:** /app/:mailbox\_id/compliance/assistant  
* **Design Philosophy:** "Tunnel" layout with no navigation. One question per screen to reduce friction.  
* **Phase 1 (Handoff):** "Verify your Photo ID." Display a **QR Code** to allow users to snap their ID on their phone, which instantly syncs to the desktop.  
* **Phase 2 (Smart Address):** Google Places Autocomplete to reduce typing errors.  
* **Phase 3 (Digital Signature):** Large, smoothed canvas for signing (replaces Notary requirement).

### **4.2 Customer Dashboard ("Inbox")**

* **Route:** /app/:mailbox\_id/mail  
* **Concept:** "The Digital Mailroom." Spacious and visual.  
* **View Toggle:** Grid (Default) vs. List.  
* **Card Component:** Aspect ratio matches a standard envelope.  
  * **Top 2/3:** High-res thumbnail.  
  * **Bottom 1/3:** Metadata footer (Sender, Date, Status Pill).  
* **Empty State:** Custom line-illustration of an empty wire basket. Headline: "No snail mail found."

### **4.3 Request Confirmation**

* **Interaction:** When a Mailbox Manager requests an action (e.g., Open & Scan), use a clean **Modal/Dialog**.  
* **Content:** Clearly display any fees (e.g., "$2.00") before the "Confirm" button to ensure transparency.

### 4.4 Customer Request Status & Deliverables

Routes:  
• /app/:mailbox\_id/requests (list)  
• /app/:mailbox\_id/requests/:request\_id (detail)  
Mailbox Manager must be able to see (a) that the request was submitted, (b) current status, and (c) completed artifacts.

### Forward Mail – customer view

### Open & Scan – customer view

• After submit: confirmation modal; indicate expected turnaround time (configurable).  
• In progress: status pill \= Processing; show “Files pending upload”.  
• Completed: show secure download links for PDFs/images (signed URLs); optionally show page thumbnails.  
• After submit: show confirmation with destination address \+ selected carrier (if customer chooses) or “TBD by staff”.  
• In progress: status pill \= Processing; show last update time.  
• Completed: show tracking number \+ downloadable label/receipt if enabled.

## 5\. Interaction Standards (Applies to Admin & Customer)

Loading: Use skeleton loaders for tables/cards; never show empty white screens.  
Empty states: Provide a friendly explanation \+ primary CTA.  
Errors: Inline field errors for forms; toast for transient errors; retry action where possible.  
Destructive actions: Require confirmation modal \+ typed confirm for irreversible actions (e.g., shred).  
Notifications: Toasts for immediate feedback; email/in-app for request completion; badge counts in nav.

## 6\. Accessibility & Quality Bar

Keyboard: All primary flows must be usable via keyboard (tab order, CMD/CTRL+K palette).  
Contrast: Status pills must meet WCAG AA for text.  
Images: Provide zoom controls; never require pixel-perfect dragging for basic use.  
Forms: Proper labels, error messages, and focus states.

## 7\. Design-to-Dev Handoff

Tokens: Maintain a single token source (JSON) consumed by web apps.  
Components: Implement in a shared component library (Storybook) with docs.  
Change control: UI changes that affect behavior must update Build Spec acceptance criteria.  
Versioning: Bump UI/UX spec minor version for new components/patterns; bump major for visual system changes.
